content.description: Middle crack system. Easy blocks to stand on for most of the way. Small, blocky overhang at the end of the route which finishes a foot to the right of an evergreen.  This could maybe be considered a harder climb because of the roof, but is an incredibly easy lead.  Pass this one by unless you are bored and just want to bag another climb to the top. Sin Sentido means "pointless" in spanish.
content.protection: its a 5.1 = anything. Think I used a hex
content.location: in small picnic shelter. directly below an evergreen growing at the edge of the top and hanging over.
5ft right of Hand Jamwhich and Offwidth Soup

content.description: easy lead but not too much protection if I remember right. warmup climb
content.protection: set of stoppers should do it with trees for anchors
content.location: crack in face to the right of Sin Sintido

content.description: This climb is contrived and can be made much easier...but this isn't the Black Hills so...why not. Use hand/fist jams for a little more than half of the climb, then 7 or so feet of offwidth. ONLY the crack is on route! use anything outside of the crack and you are either cheating or lying.
content.protection: lead - hand/fist sized cams for the first section.  A small wire to the right before the offwidth...then to the top
content.location: first dihedral to the left when you walk into the trees.  hidden just above and right of a stump.
easy climb to the right of side of satisfaction

content.protection: variety of gear. i used a #3 bd...hence the name

content.description: Climber's right of Postitron.  Includes right wall of picnic cove and heads into the trees to the right.
